I heard horror stories from past group members urging me never to take a course with this prof and I listened to them in the past but in my last year I had no choice as this class fit my schedule perfectly. I was worried for no reason and honestly questioned the validity of what others have said about him. Easy A + he's big on group work, nice guy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Group projects', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Professor Park's biggest problem is clarity. He seems to have a difficult time explaining himself and when questioned about it, he can get defensive. He doesn't seem to be very organized and frequently changed due dates. As for the grading criteria, it's pretty much a guessing game, basically hit or miss.

Assignments don't make sense, grammatically they are full of errors. His expectations are not clear and his feedback is little to none. Slow at marking and only 3o students, half of which dropped out. Lectures are repetitive and we are tested and evaluated on to topics not covered. Very rude to students and doesn't follow course description

OMG. don't even try, seriously you will want to cry. he taught the class completely wrong and will constantly make you feel awful. all he does is yell and call people out personally to make them feel bad infront of the whole class. assignments dont have a rubric, and is full of spelling errors & if you try and email him about it he wont answer it.
Do not take a course if he is the prof. very unorganized and very unclear. Assignments rarely relate to the lectures. Slides are 200 pages long and don't talk about anything. No textbook.

Participation matters but he does not make it clear what you need to do to get the participation marks (i.e. just be present in class or to talk in class).

Prof Park took a less than interesting subject and did the best he could, which paid off. He is  super nice guy and despite his accent his lectures are interesting. Assignments and the exam were reasonable, although having to do 2 full census reports and a group project was definitely enough work. Attendance is taken.  Overall pretty decent!
Passionate about his field and the topics discussed in class. Lots of repetition in his lectures, but if that doesn't bother you, go to class and you'll do just fine.

RUN! I wouldn't say this is a bird course (Science Major). Yes the material is very straightforward, it's the prof that makes it difficult. Impossible to get time with him outside class hours. The TA is your friend, ask  for clarity on the assignments (50% of mark) bc prof is extremely picky. At the end I got a good grade no clue how I got it!

He is a horrible professor and I didn't like him at all. His assignments are unclear and he enjoys making his students feel bad when they ask questions. He doesn't reply to emails and he doesn't care about his students. He never posts marks on Black Board learn and his assignments are always marked late. His final exam was also hard and confusing.

He is tough to understand, gives out a bunch of assignments with no clear grading criteria and his tests are tough. He doesn't give out marks. Instead he gives you a letter for your grade so he can change your grade later. He asks his TA's to give out a B average. Then somehow everyone got a higher mark in the end. He bell curved one assignment
He's a funny guide and his exam was really easy. His class was not the most organized though. His assignments were easy but included little instructions/directions/
Terrible at explaining everything and doesn't give you anything to study for the final exam except for a list of words he's never even mentioned in class.

This class was interesting, he demands respect from students during lectures. Assignments given throughout helps with grade, they're very easy. Midterm and final were easy as well. Attend class, read and follow the study guide given for class and you'll be fine! Don't bother trying to write everything down, he will post all the slides before test

Great prof! Can get mad when students annoy him but just respect him and don't talk during the entire lecture. Gives participation marks which is always an easy bonus! Assignments are clear and he answers questions in emails or in person really well. Put a little effort and use your textbook for an easy A on assignments! Gives study guides!

Jungwee Park is halarious! He adds alot of slides a little last minute but they are great reviews of the chapters and gives study guides. Answers emails quickly and is willing to meet outside his office hours. Four assignments and one essay type which boost your grades. Make sure to add alot of material from the textbook! Very straight forward prof

This professor does not care about his students at all. Assignments are super unclear and irrelevant to course material. He tends to get off topic and is super rude. The TA's are also super hard markers.. Avoid at all cost..... you have been warned.

This professor is horrible.  I don't even know where to start.  Unclear assignments and gets bad grade because there were no guidelines.  Lectures are extremely boring. rComments: assignments with unclear instructions, will maybe go through 5 slides in class before he goes off topic (on a lucky day), never seem to know what he wants from us, theres a TA that only answers emails twice a week, posts lecture slides (all out of order) a few days before the midterm and the final wth new material.

THE WORST PROFESSOR I'VE EVER HAD IN UNIVERSITY (I'm 4th year BSc). Completely rude and condescending. EXTREMELY unclear. rComments: Weekly assignments, participation marks and a final exam (worth 50%).  He tries to make the course interesting, stats is a very dry course. Lot of assignments to make up marks. Heavy use of the textbook. Weekly assignments are very interesting. If you study hard, you can get a B.

Park is unclear with almost every aspect of this course. He is completely disorganized, unwilling to answer your questions, and if he does he is completely condescending and rude. He has weekly assignments that the grading scheme makes no sense for, group projects, midterms and a final paper. He is unapproachable for help. DO NOT GET HIM.

The syllabus is garbage pay attention to his announcements on virtual campus. He doesn't really understand questions from students, and if you constantly ask the same questions to clarify , he will loose his temper and yell at you. He isn't a good prof ,but if you do the work you should pass. Summary assignments every week to help gain marks.

Does not give any feedback on assignments(literally 0). Very unclear as a professor. Absolutely terrible. Gives little to no direction for tests, essays, or group presentations. Asks for your home address (why??) and claims to memorize everyone's name (he doesn't). Lectures do not reflect anything on his slides and also do not reflect anything on the test. Teach yourself from the textbook, that's where he pulls all his exam qs

I have had Professor Park multiple times during my time at the University of Ottawa. First, he is very educated and well-spoken. Second, he is hilarious. Third, he is very fair. Highly recommend taking a class with him. All you need to do is show up to his class and pay attention and you will end up with a good mark.
Life course events course: Park is a very enthusiastic teacher. I enjoyed his lectures, learned much from presentations. I feel that this course was a good educational experience.
Professor Park is very clear in his teaching. He has a great class organization.
The course was fun, informative and inclusive. Park is an enthusiastic teacher.

Dead boring, incoherent lectures, with mandatory attendence. He makes students do presentations so he doesn't have to. His assignments and midterms are also ridiculous, not reflecting what you learned, and he is shockingly unhelpful and uncooperative if you have any questions or issues outside of class. Definitely avoid him if you can. :/

This class a waste of time. The lectures were an incoherent, incomprehensible mess and the assignments and exam did not reflect the material covered in class. I can honestly say there was no value in this course and that I did not learn anything, other than that I should follow my instincts when I consider dropping something the first week of term.

The prof is all over the place during class. He doesn't use his ppt (doesn't post up the slides either). Spends the entire 3 hour lecture playing a movie or giving examples. I didn't learn anything new (everything was common knowledge). I did like that marking was distributed among assignments, attendance, book report, group presentation.

I find Professor Park to be very well spoken, and to always convey his message clearly. He is a wonderful prof, and makes this theory course even more interesting. I would recommend this to anyone as well as any courses taught by this prof.
I liked Park's enthusiasm and good humor. He makes students to actively participate in the class; he demonstrates great knowledge in the class.

He goes off-topic so frequently that I usually have the urge to get up and leave class. It is like the Jungwee Park Comedy Show every lecture. I do not know if he is a smart man, considering his lectures are almost 100% based on the textbook. He is also difficult to understand sometimes due to his accent. How do people like him get to teach?

Park is a straight-shooter, he tells it as it is. Average lecturer, not too bad. Gave out a lot of assignments. Not afraid to call people out for disrupting. All in all, Park is an average prof, stick with him if ya have him.

Some students have bad things to say about Prof Park BUT I've had him for methods and stats and I very much respect him, and his course format. Instead of putting all the weight onto exams, he spreads work out into weekly assignments, allowing students more control over their grades & time to really digest material. He also has a sense of humour.
It was an easy and interesting course. I did just put a little bit of extra effort and gained an A+. Durkheim is cool.

Durkheim class: super boring but you get up to 15% for attendance. he is hard to understand and his lectures are boring but it is easy to do well. he has weekly summaries you have to hand in which are awful to do but again worth 15%, so easy marks. i did the minimum and got a B+. i recommend him only because you can slack off and still do well
This is a great soc. stat course. Weekly assignments were helpful and the professor made numbers quite interesting to learn.
I think he's a very good lecturer. He know a lot and is clear about things he's explaining. This course opened my eyes to a broader understanding who people are and why they are the way they are.
Very enthusiastic teacher. I enjoyed his lectures, they were easy to follow. Enjoyed learning more about different ethnicities and I feel that this course was a good educational experience.
FUN'N EASY COURSE ON HEALTH SOCIOLOGY. KEEPING HEALTH JOURNAL WAS INTERESTING!
this prof is strict, but i gotta tell i learned a lot.

Not the worst proffesor ive had. Hit and miss if he would do a good job teaching the topic. Assignments were very useful to the subject matter.The 15% attendance mark is stupid and he couldnt even explain how he calculated it.

WARNING: Avoid this Prof at all costs, it`s for your own good. I`ve had nothing but problems and unanswered questions from this guy. If you like your GPA nice and high, then stay away from this course with this prof.

This is the 2nd course I take w/ Mr. Park and I have benefitted greatly.

He is a very nice teacher...and his assignments and tests are very straight forward. He is very helpful if you have any questions!
